WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.960 --> 00:00:05.808
(mystical music)

2
00:00:12.405 --> 00:00:14.399
<v ->Of all the religions of the world, one of the</v>

3
00:00:14.399 --> 00:00:16.427
most mystical is that of Sufism.

4
00:00:16.427 --> 00:00:18.580
It's roots are Islamic, and the practice

5
00:00:18.580 --> 00:00:20.043
is one of the heart.

6
00:00:20.043 --> 00:00:23.156
Shaikh Kabir Helminski was the first Westerner recognized

7
00:00:23.156 --> 00:00:27.061
as a shake or elder in the the Mevlevi order of Sufism

8
00:00:27.061 --> 00:00:28.937
which dates back to the 13th century

9
00:00:28.937 --> 00:00:30.868
and is based on the works of the great poet

10
00:00:30.868 --> 00:00:32.447
and philosopher, Rumi.

11
00:00:32.447 --> 00:00:34.378
In the West we know a little of this tradition

12
00:00:34.378 --> 00:00:36.233
other than the beautiful poems of Rumi

13
00:00:36.233 --> 00:00:38.068
which have been excerpted to appear

14
00:00:38.068 --> 00:00:39.199
on greeting cards.

15
00:00:39.199 --> 00:00:41.855
Here Shaikh Helminski explains that among other things,

16
00:00:41.855 --> 00:00:44.493
Sufism has been at the heart of Islam,

17
00:00:44.499 --> 00:00:47.138
but has been marginalized somewhat by extremism.

18
00:00:54.760 --> 00:00:56.990
I would like it if you could begin to tell me about

19
00:00:56.990 --> 00:00:59.816
the essence of this Sufi way.

20
00:01:02.077 --> 00:01:06.141
<v ->Let's start with Rumi since he has been the major</v>

21
00:01:06.141 --> 00:01:09.846
voice of Sufism in the West recently,

22
00:01:10.813 --> 00:01:13.472
and very popular, very beloved.

23
00:01:13.617 --> 00:01:16.658
People intuitively sense that there's something here

24
00:01:16.658 --> 00:01:21.658
of beauty and value, but Rumi was not unique

25
00:01:22.598 --> 00:01:26.358
or even innovative in the Sufi tradition.

26
00:01:26.832 --> 00:01:28.747
He's completely exemplary.

27
00:01:29.104 --> 00:01:31.766
He's an organic outgrowth

28
00:01:32.123 --> 00:01:35.162
of a tradition that goes back

29
00:01:35.162 --> 00:01:37.012
to the prophet Mohammad.

30
00:01:37.274 --> 00:01:38.714
Peace and blessings upon him

31
00:01:38.714 --> 00:01:41.318
and the revelation of the Quarn.

32
00:01:41.318 --> 00:01:43.962
Some people have suggested that Sufism

33
00:01:43.962 --> 00:01:46.398
predates Islam.

34
00:01:47.612 --> 00:01:50.256
If they mean mysticism predated it,

35
00:01:50.256 --> 00:01:53.503
Islam, of course,

36
00:01:54.202 --> 00:01:57.413
but the qualities that we associate with Sufism

37
00:01:57.413 --> 00:02:02.413
really were exemplified beginning with

38
00:02:02.659 --> 00:02:05.811
the prophet and the

39
00:02:06.019 --> 00:02:08.622
revelation that came through him,

40
00:02:08.622 --> 00:02:11.198
and particularly the language, the metaphysics,

41
00:02:11.523 --> 00:02:15.283
the vocabulary, the context

42
00:02:15.821 --> 00:02:17.159
was all

43
00:02:18.008 --> 00:02:21.672
established about 14 centuries ago,

44
00:02:22.295 --> 00:02:25.015
and Rumi and other great Sufis

45
00:02:25.015 --> 00:02:29.452
are organic outgrowths of that.

46
00:02:29.452 --> 00:02:32.162
They're almost like fractals of that original

47
00:02:32.162 --> 00:02:35.526
truth or revelation.

48
00:02:37.889 --> 00:02:42.209
Rumi is exemplary of his spirituality that

49
00:02:42.209 --> 00:02:45.521
is very much grounded in life

50
00:02:45.644 --> 00:02:50.644
integrated with our humanness, and I think that's

51
00:02:50.795 --> 00:02:52.310
one of the attractions.

52
00:02:52.310 --> 00:02:56.118
