276
00:15:20.865 --> 00:15:23.835
and have had an honored place

277
00:15:23.905 --> 00:15:25.893
within Islam.

278
00:15:26.347 --> 00:15:30.219
Although in recent times for various reasons,

279
00:15:30.219 --> 00:15:35.219
Sufism has been more marginalized in Islamic cultures

280
00:15:35.979 --> 00:15:38.026
because of two factors.

281
00:15:38.026 --> 00:15:42.271
One is because of modernism with it's emphasis

282
00:15:42.271 --> 00:15:45.290
on science and materialism

283
00:15:45.290 --> 00:15:47.747
which affected even Islamic thinking,

284
00:15:47.818 --> 00:15:52.552
and also extremism and fundamentalism

285
00:15:52.552 --> 00:15:57.144
which is in some ways

286
00:15:57.343 --> 00:16:00.733
a new phenomena, a relatively new phenomena in Islam,

287
00:16:00.733 --> 00:16:03.794
and this has caused the marginalization

288
00:16:03.794 --> 00:16:07.554
of Sufism in the most modern times,

289
00:16:07.977 --> 00:16:12.977
but traditionally Islam has been a civilization

290
00:16:13.480 --> 00:16:17.512
which mysticism has come very close to the surface

291
00:16:17.512 --> 00:16:19.601
you might say.

292
00:16:19.601 --> 00:16:24.338
And it's partly because there are many features

293
00:16:24.338 --> 00:16:27.638
many aspects of Islam that are

294
00:16:28.221 --> 00:16:30.188
exclusively mystical.

295
00:16:30.236 --> 00:16:33.420
For instance, people talk about,

296
00:16:33.703 --> 00:16:38.044
imagine that the Quran could be read

297
00:16:38.044 --> 00:16:40.316
in a literalistic way, the way some people

298
00:16:40.316 --> 00:16:41.962
read the Bible.

299
00:16:42.289 --> 00:16:44.870
If you're going to take the Quran literally,

300
00:16:44.870 --> 00:16:47.793
how are you going to deal with

301
00:16:47.793 --> 00:16:49.642
a verse like this,

302
00:16:49.905 --> 00:16:53.824
to God belongs the East and the West,

303
00:16:53.904 --> 00:16:57.418
and wheresoever you look is the face of God.

304
00:16:58.074 --> 00:16:59.771
How could you understand that literally?

305
00:16:59.771 --> 00:17:02.053
You could be a raving mystic

306
00:17:02.053 --> 00:17:06.020
to accept that proposition, or another example,

307
00:17:06.020 --> 00:17:08.249
Muslims pray five times a day.

308
00:17:08.249 --> 00:17:10.874
They do a series of standing, bowing,

309
00:17:10.874 --> 00:17:12.095
and prostrating.

310
00:17:13.843 --> 00:17:15.283
What are they prostrating to?

311
00:17:15.566 --> 00:17:18.537
A religious institution, a human being?

312
00:17:18.895 --> 00:17:22.365
No, they're standing before the infinite,

313
00:17:22.371 --> 00:17:25.668
and they're putting all their worldly concerns

314
00:17:25.668 --> 00:17:28.359
and preoccupations behind them,

315
00:17:28.409 --> 00:17:31.107
and they're saying the divinity

316
00:17:31.107 --> 00:17:33.842
is greater than everything,

317
00:17:33.891 --> 00:17:37.208
and they hopefully are remembering the

318
00:17:37.208 --> 00:17:41.340
advice of the prophet Mohammad who said

319
00:17:41.548 --> 00:17:45.496
the ritual prayer is only valid

320
00:17:45.496 --> 00:17:46.983
with presence.

321
00:17:47.938 --> 00:17:49.261
<v Woman>True, if you're going through it by wrote,</v>

322
00:17:49.261 --> 00:17:50.486
it has no meaning.

323
00:17:50.486 --> 00:17:53.421
<v ->The ritual prayer itself even at the level</v>

324
00:17:53.421 --> 00:17:56.854
of enteric Islam becomes an exercise

325
00:17:56.854 --> 00:17:58.054
in mindfulness.

326
00:17:58.668 --> 00:18:02.379
In many ways, Sufism

327
00:18:02.379 --> 00:18:06.741
is not exactly the same as the outer

328
00:18:06.741 --> 00:18:11.189
religion of Islam, but it has been a path,

329
00:18:11.189 --> 00:18:13.231
what we call a perica,

330
00:18:13.332 --> 00:18:16.532
and it's explicitly recognized as

331
00:18:16.532 --> 00:18:19.253
a path for those

332
00:18:19.253 --> 00:18:22.250
who seek more than

333
00:18:22.250 --> 00:18:26.175
nominal belonging to a religion,

334
00:18:26.175 --> 00:18:28.607
to those kinds of souls

335
00:18:28.607 --> 00:18:31.070
who have a contemplative and

336
00:18:31.070 --> 00:18:33.161
transformational calling,

337
00:18:33.161 --> 00:18:37.427
and Sufi orders particularly since

338
00:18:37.427 --> 00:18:40.957
the 12th century have been pervasive

339
00:18:40.957 --> 00:18:42.281
in the Islamic world.

340
00:18:42.281 --> 00:18:44.914
They're just a part of life, and

341
00:18:44.914 --> 00:18:48.225
<v Woman>And this is really non-exclusive in nature</v>

342
00:18:48.225 --> 00:18:49.996
and global.

343
00:18:49.996 --> 00:18:50.552
<v ->It's global.</v>

344
00:18:50.552 --> 00:18:53.447
It's non-exclusive, and

345
00:18:54.125 --> 00:18:59.125
it's an accepted part

346
00:18:59.553 --> 00:19:02.199
of common consciousness

347
00:19:02.199 --> 00:19:06.001
that some people will be called to this

348
00:19:07.521 --> 00:19:09.909
transformational contemplative way of life

349
00:19:09.909 --> 00:19:14.909
while still having families, holding down a job,

350
00:19:15.040 --> 00:19:17.366
doing the practical things of life.

351
00:19:19.596 --> 00:19:22.966
This has been a beautiful side, a very enriching side

352
00:19:22.966 --> 00:19:26.037
of Islamic civilization.

353
00:19:26.037 --> 00:19:31.037
Recently, the king of Morocco called a thousand sufi shakes.

354
00:19:32.490 --> 00:19:35.529
This was a few months ago, and I was there.

355
00:19:37.179 --> 00:19:39.832
