356
00:19:40.201 --> 00:19:44.077
that sufis should be allowed to do their work,

357
00:19:44.639 --> 00:19:49.639
that they work for the betterment of human souls

358
00:19:49.960 --> 00:19:53.827
which ultimately benefits cultures,

359
00:19:54.324 --> 00:19:58.359
and they should not be instrumentalized politically

360
00:19:58.409 --> 00:20:01.608
to serve any political purpose, but should be

361
00:20:01.608 --> 00:20:04.210
protected and allowed to do the work

362
00:20:04.210 --> 00:20:06.343
that traditionally they do.

363
00:20:06.343 --> 00:20:07.901
I had the great pleasure of being together

364
00:20:07.901 --> 00:20:12.733
with about 1,000 sufi shakes and scholars.

365
00:20:12.733 --> 00:20:15.466
A third of them were from black Africa.

366
00:20:15.750 --> 00:20:17.482
A third of them were from the Arab world,

367
00:20:17.670 --> 00:20:20.572
and a third of them were from everywhere else

368
00:20:20.572 --> 00:20:23.174
including California and France,

369
00:20:23.174 --> 00:20:25.984
and even China.

370
00:20:26.586 --> 00:20:30.555
It was a great affirmation that sufis

371
00:20:30.555 --> 00:20:34.314
have a place, and that

372
00:20:34.874 --> 00:20:38.121
their work is needed

373
00:20:38.224 --> 00:20:40.933
in todays world, and can

374
00:20:40.933 --> 00:20:43.720
contribute to stability

375
00:20:43.982 --> 00:20:48.222
of societies at a time when

376
00:20:48.270 --> 00:20:51.027
there are a lot of destabilizing factors,

377
00:20:51.033 --> 00:20:52.680
particularly extremism.

378
00:20:53.156 --> 00:20:54.168
<v Woman>Of all kinds.</v>

379
00:20:54.168 --> 00:20:58.447
<v ->Yeah, and one of my friends, Cideamid Coastis</v>

380
00:20:58.447 --> 00:21:01.624
who is the assistant minister for religious affairs

