00:21:01.624 --> 00:21:04.483
in Morocco now has been given a TV program

382
00:21:04.483 --> 00:21:06.867
in Morocco where he talks about

383
00:21:06.947 --> 00:21:11.697
I'd say sufi character, and

384
00:21:11.822 --> 00:21:16.578
extremists who have never for some reason,

385
00:21:16.578 --> 00:21:19.042
they are mostly ignorant people

386
00:21:19.042 --> 00:21:21.863
are being exposed to the beauties of

387
00:21:22.008 --> 00:21:26.658
the teachings on character, and the sweetness

388
00:21:26.658 --> 00:21:29.026
of the sufi heart, and

389
00:21:29.026 --> 00:21:33.361
it's a very beneficial thing

390
00:21:33.431 --> 00:21:36.145
for that society at this time.

391
00:21:36.566 --> 00:21:38.497
<v Woman>And it seems that it's important for us</v>

392
00:21:38.497 --> 00:21:41.047
to understand something here, and you already

393
00:21:41.047 --> 00:21:43.802
touched on this when you were talking about

394
00:21:43.905 --> 00:21:46.689
the prayer five times a day.

395
00:21:46.689 --> 00:21:51.179
This doesn't have to do with minimizing oneself

396
00:21:51.179 --> 00:21:53.942
as a human being before

397
00:21:53.942 --> 00:21:55.258
a deity.

398
00:21:55.606 --> 00:21:59.925
This really is about remembering that aspect

399
00:21:59.925 --> 00:22:02.901
within the self, and there is a line

400
00:22:02.901 --> 00:22:05.824
by Rumi that I just love, and it had to do

401
00:22:05.824 --> 00:22:08.820
with knock and the door will be open unto you,

402
00:22:08.820 --> 00:22:11.349
and he was saying, I knocked and the door was open,

403
00:22:11.349 --> 00:22:14.623
and then I realized I was knocking from the inside,

404
00:22:14.623 --> 00:22:19.433
meaning we already are that, but we have forgotten

405
00:22:19.433 --> 00:22:20.916
that we already are that, and this is

406
00:22:20.916 --> 00:22:23.583
an awakening and remembering as much as anything.

407
00:22:23.583 --> 00:22:24.232
Is it not?

408
00:22:26.078 --> 00:22:27.331
<v ->That's a good point.</v>

409
00:22:27.752 --> 00:22:29.486
If we look at the prayer,

410
00:22:29.609 --> 00:22:33.431
and you see that people are standing in rows

411
00:22:34.248 --> 00:22:36.940
and they're bowing, and they prostrating.

412
00:22:37.107 --> 00:22:41.192
When they stand, this is a meditative posture

413
00:22:41.192 --> 00:22:46.192
of accepting our human responsibility

414
00:22:46.321 --> 00:22:50.656
as caretakers and as representatives

415
00:22:51.154 --> 00:22:53.952
of the divine in this world.

416
00:22:54.781 --> 00:22:58.098
The bowing reminds us that we're

417
00:22:58.098 --> 00:23:02.550
also servants of creation and each other.

418
00:23:02.598 --> 00:23:07.598
The prostration is a prostration not to any human authority

419
00:23:08.827 --> 00:23:11.722
or human formulation.

420
00:23:12.145 --> 00:23:15.455
The prostration is toward the real,

421
00:23:15.718 --> 00:23:19.028
towards the highest truth itself

422
00:23:19.344 --> 00:23:22.592
and acknowledging that where we

423
00:23:22.821 --> 00:23:25.445
assume the responsibility and authority

424
00:23:25.445 --> 00:23:28.159
in the world, we openly

425
00:23:28.325 --> 00:23:32.665
are surrendered to

426
00:23:32.665 --> 00:23:35.781
the beauty, the grace,

427
00:23:35.781 --> 00:23:38.820
and the power of the divine

428
00:23:38.820 --> 00:23:41.775
without which we would be nothing.

429
00:23:41.775 --> 00:23:44.718
All of our faculties are gifts of the divine.

430
00:23:44.718 --> 00:23:47.160
<v Woman>We'd have no knowing beauty.</v>

431
00:23:47.160 --> 00:23:49.449
<v ->Right, right, so we</v>

432
00:23:50.200 --> 00:23:53.124
we are in awe of the beauty of the divine

433
00:23:53.124 --> 00:23:54.820
more than anything else,

434
00:23:54.820 --> 00:23:59.789
and Sufism is a process it's understood as a process of

435
00:23:59.789 --> 00:24:04.188
purifying the heart so that

436
00:24:04.622 --> 00:24:09.622
we perceive, we reach a level of spiritual perception

437
00:24:09.698 --> 00:24:14.698
relatively free of the distortions of egoism, but

438
00:24:15.948 --> 00:24:20.823
the teachings on ego in sufism I think are very practical,

439
00:24:20.823 --> 00:24:24.395
because we don't talk about

440
00:24:24.395 --> 00:24:28.875
destroying the self, and we don't talk about being without

441
00:24:28.875 --> 00:24:32.966
a self, but we do talk about seven levels of the self,

442
00:24:33.132 --> 00:24:38.102
and at the lowest level, the self is in a prison

443
00:24:38.102 --> 00:24:40.325
of compulsions and

444
00:24:40.417 --> 00:24:42.581
<v Woman>Addictions and what not.</v>

445
00:24:44.933 --> 00:24:48.102
<v ->And we move through various levels of subtlization</v>

446
00:24:48.812 --> 00:24:51.940
second level is a stage of

447
00:24:53.408 --> 00:24:56.628
feeling some conscience, awakening of conscience.

448
00:24:56.628 --> 00:24:59.342
The third stage is reaching,

449
00:24:59.904 --> 00:25:02.720
becoming a functioning healthy ego,

450
00:25:02.720 --> 00:25:04.244
a positive human being.

451
00:25:04.244 --> 00:25:07.989
What would be considered salvation in religious terms.

452
00:25:07.989 --> 00:25:11.071
The fourth level of the self in Sufism

453
00:25:11.071 --> 00:25:15.347
is the beginning of awakening into consciousness,

454
00:25:15.347 --> 00:25:17.897
mindfulness, presence.

455
00:25:17.897 --> 00:25:21.172
This is where most of the eserteric teachings begin.

456
00:25:23.899 --> 00:25:27.902
It can be a long phase of our practice

457
00:25:28.261 --> 00:25:31.785
to introduce presence and awareness

458
00:25:31.951 --> 00:25:35.343
into every breath, every action, every relationship.

459
00:25:35.343 --> 00:25:37.850
The fifth level is

460
00:25:37.850 --> 00:25:42.850
experiencing unity or intimacy with the divine,

461
00:25:43.258 --> 00:25:45.935
where we have a lived experience

462
00:25:45.935 --> 00:25:50.532
of how everything we are is sourced in the divine.

463
00:25:50.532 --> 00:25:52.804
It's only the fifth stage.

464
00:25:52.804 --> 00:25:55.545
The sixth stage, and I'm going through this as concisely

465
00:25:55.545 --> 00:25:56.334
as I can.

466
00:25:56.334 --> 00:25:59.859
The point being that we always have some

467
00:26:00.141 --> 00:26:03.075
experience of I ness at all these stages.

468
00:26:03.075 --> 00:26:05.303
The sixth stage is when you turn back

469
00:26:05.303 --> 00:26:09.250
from that unity and return to this world

470
00:26:09.250 --> 00:26:13.703
with all of it's conflicts, joys and disappointments,

471
00:26:13.986 --> 00:26:17.496
but with that illumination,

472
00:26:17.496 --> 00:26:19.921
with that awareness that

473
00:26:19.980 --> 00:26:22.114
the divine is closer to us than our

474
00:26:22.114 --> 00:26:23.554
jugular vein.

475
00:26:23.554 --> 00:26:26.807
The sixth stage is almost like

476
00:26:26.807 --> 00:26:28.247
crucifixion.

477
00:26:28.247 --> 00:26:30.976
It's when you experience all the suffering

478
00:26:30.976 --> 00:26:35.723
of life, but without losing your awareness of being

479
00:26:35.723 --> 00:26:37.504
sourced in the divine.

480
00:26:37.504 --> 00:26:39.670
The seventh stage is

481
00:26:39.670 --> 00:26:44.670
being an ordinary human being,

482
00:26:44.939 --> 00:26:49.939
invisible, anonymous, but with

483
00:26:50.165 --> 00:26:51.509
purity of heart,

484
00:26:51.509 --> 00:26:56.509
grounded in this life, but integrating

485
00:26:57.385 --> 00:27:01.443
all levels of consciousness

486
00:27:01.727 --> 00:27:05.048
in that life, but always

487
00:27:05.054 --> 00:27:07.999
the sense of I is transformed.

488
00:27:07.999 --> 00:27:10.922
In the early stages, you were like ice.

489
00:27:10.922 --> 00:27:13.438
You're like a block of ice.

490
00:27:13.438 --> 00:27:15.918
At another stage you melt into water,

491
00:27:16.009 --> 00:27:17.896
the I melts into water.

492
00:27:17.896 --> 00:27:21.118
At another stage it becomes it's steamy, vaporous,

493
00:27:21.118 --> 00:27:23.539
and finally at the highest stage,

494
00:27:23.539 --> 00:27:26.622
it's almost as if one's sense of I

495
00:27:26.622 --> 00:27:29.917
while being locatable

496
00:27:29.917 --> 00:27:34.611
as a person, also has at least an aspect

497
00:27:34.611 --> 00:27:36.840
which is more like humidity.

498
00:27:36.840 --> 00:27:38.481
You sense that your identity

499
00:27:38.481 --> 00:27:42.545
extends in some sense through the universe,

500
00:27:42.545 --> 00:27:47.516
and is in every other me and in every other self,

501
00:27:47.516 --> 00:27:51.142
but still there's always a sense

502
00:27:51.142 --> 00:27:55.227
an ever subtler, more comprehensive sense of self,

503
00:27:55.227 --> 00:27:58.151
so that the self is like the drop.

504
00:27:58.151 --> 00:28:00.262
It doesn't dissolve in the ocean.

505
00:28:00.262 --> 00:28:03.280
The drop realizes it contains the ocean,

506
00:28:03.280 --> 00:28:06.554
and the drop can choose.

507
00:28:06.554 --> 00:28:08.625
The drop that has reached a certain level

508
00:28:08.625 --> 00:28:13.295
of spiritual maturity can be at will

509
00:28:13.295 --> 00:28:15.332
the drop or the ocean depending on

510
00:28:15.332 --> 00:28:17.957
what the need is at that moment.

511
00:28:17.957 --> 00:28:19.375
<v Woman>And that's why you're at the science in</v>

512
00:28:19.375 --> 00:28:21.647
non-duality conference.

513
00:28:21.647 --> 00:28:22.276
<v ->Yes.</v>

514
00:28:22.276 --> 00:28:26.319
<v Woman>As I was listening to you go through the seven</v>

515
00:28:26.319 --> 00:28:30.105
phases, it seems to me

516
00:28:30.105 --> 00:28:33.027
that Rumi appeared to be writing a lot

517
00:28:33.027 --> 00:28:35.353
of his most well known works from

